==English==
===Pronunciation===
*tô(r)-nā'dō, /tɔː(r)ˈneɪd@ʊ/, /tO:(r)"neId@U/
*[[WEAE]] /toɹˈnaɪ.do/

===Etymology===
From Spanish or Portuguese [[tornar]] to turn, return, Latin [[tornare]] to turn, hence, a whirling  wind. The Spanish & Portuguese [[tornada]] is a return.  See [[Turn]].

===Noun===
'''tornado''' ([[tornadoes]] or [[tornados]])
# A violent whirling wind; specifically (Meteorology), a tempest  distinguished by a rapid whirling and slow progressive  motion, usually accompaned with severe thunder, lightning, and torrents of rain, and commonly of short duration and  small breadth; a small cyclone.
